reviews.review_text: Its McDonalds! I come here for the best ice coffees esp when theyre $1 during the summers! I also think their junior chicken burgers are better than the McChicken burgers. This has generated substantial debate!
I end up here like 3 times a month. Staff has always been really nice, polite, and fast.
There is a gentleman by the name of Ramon who works cash, he needs a raise! He is cordial, professional and always gets my order right
Phone was unplugged and relocated while charging.. Manager didnt check the cameras for the customer ... Hmmmmm Wheelchair accessibility: KOHO app, use this code 4VSLW9M8
Good service, the guy at the till is always great.  Small location, but always busy.  Food was fresh, no complaints!
This McD is awesome - friendly staff members and they acknowledge you the moment they spot you. Clean and i have been coming often. Will definitely recommend over Kingsway by highgate

McDonalds is really expensive.  They charge $11.00 for a large big mac. I places a special order of no mac sauce  but plan chicken sauce instead. And no lettuce. When l hot my order. It had the wrong sauce and had extra lettuce.  It took 3 time returning it to the counter. I just got my money back and went to Burger King for two fresh whoppers for $8.00. This is not the first time my orders was incorrect.  I even phoned McDonalds head office to complain. But nothing has changed. This will be the last visit to McDonalds.  No l do not recommend this McDonalds

The  McDs has THE BEST STAFF. They are all so kind and patient and hard working. Its amazing that they are so friendly, considering that the are has some of the worst customers I have ever seen. Keep your heads, up guys, you are doing great and we find you so amazing and impressive considering the abuse you receive.
First experience there and I really like how the staff organized specially gurleen she s so organized I had a big order and everything were fresh and taste good :)

Those Philippino girls were very polite. They were offended by some racial slur from the customer before me. The manager rightfully stood up for her crew. Meanwhile, my denish was forgotten in the stove. They quickly noticed that as I was still there while their order queue was cleared. An apology was offered and, when I took my order home, I have found an extra apple pie. I am sure the pie was an intended gratitude.
The food comes quickly and fresh. Staffs are welcoming and friendly. For the price of the food, its more than enough so Im always happy to visit this restaurant.
